http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Body-stuffed-in-plastic-bag-found-in-train-toilet/article14019260.ece

A body of an unidentified woman was found stuffed in a plastic bag in the toilet of the Guntur- Hyderabad passenger train at Kachiguda early on Sunday. The woman aged 25-years was draped in maroon colour saree and pink blouse. The passenger train arrived at the Kachiguda railway station at around 11 p.m on Saturday night. On early Sunday, at around 4 a.m., while the workers were cleaning the train, they found the body in a plastic bag in the general compartment and alerted the Government Railway police Kachiguda.“The killers might have strangulated the woman at some place and stuffed it in a plastic bag. Later, they brought it into the train and kept it in the toilet,” the Kachiguda GRP said.A case under Section 302 (murder) of Indian Penal Code was registered and the body shifted to Osmania General Hospital mortuary.